    <p><font size="-1"><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b>&nbsp;</b></font><b><font color="ff3300" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><i>Still 
      Having Trouble Finding Things?</i></font>&nbsp;<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"> If so, try using the following three lists as a means of coming up with 
        searchable names and terms: (1) the <a href="wallace/wallthes.htm"><font color="3333ff">'Wallace 
          Thesaurus'</font></a> (which lists places, terms, and titles in one way 
        or another connected with Wallace (2) the <a href="wallace/names.htm"><font color="3333ff">'Personal 
          Names Index'</font></a> (which lists the names of people and corporate 
        entities found in Wallace's published writings) (3) the <a href="wallace/bib5.htm"><font color="3333ff">'General 
          Subject Index'</font></a> (which associates Wallace's published writings 
        with a list of general subjects); or (4) send me an email at: charles.smith@wku.edu .</font></b>&nbsp;<br />
      </font></p><br />
          
